  "abi_version": "1.5.0",
  "description": "Frozen ABI for libpfsf_compute v0.3d-v0.4. v1.5.0 is an additive MINOR bump over v1.4.0: adds pfsf_set_pcg_enabled(engine, int) so Java BRConfig.isPFSFPCGEnabled() can gate the native PCG tail at runtime (PR#187 Capy-ai R4). The symbol is a pure setter with no struct/enum impact. v1.4.0 introduced 4 aug-opcodes (IDs 18..21) consumed by pfsf_plan_execute. v1.3.0 added pfsf_abi_contract_version. v1.2.0 added 3 crash-handler symbols. v1.1.0 introduced 13 plan-buffer opcodes (IDs 5..17) and wired pfsf_compute_conductivity. No symbol was removed, no existing struct layout changed, no enum value was renumbered. Any future symbol removal, signature change, struct layout shift, or existing-enum-value renumbering MUST bump MAJOR to 2.",
  "pinned_on_commit": "v0.4-m2i",

